Name

Maria Theresa, Holy Roman Empress Gender: F

Birthname Maria Theresa Walburga Amalia Christina born on 13 May 1717 at 07:30 (= 07:30 AM ) Place Vienna, Austria, 48n13, 16e2223 Timezone LMT m16e2223 (is local mean time) Data source

Bio/autobiography

Rodden Rating B Collector: Scholfield

Astrology data 22°16' 21°54 Asc. 10°50'

Biography

Austrian royalty, the daughter of Kaiser Karl VI and the Queen of Bohemia and Hungary and Empress of Austria. She bore 16 children, one of whom was Marie Antoinette.

Maria Theresa died in Vienna 29 November 1780.

Source Notes

Sy Scholfield quotes "Die große Maria Theresia" by Carl August Schimmer (Vienna: Dirnböck, 1845), p. 7: "Maria Theresia wurde geboren den 13. Mai 1717 Morgens um halb 8 Uhr zu Wien- als die Erbtochter des römischdeutschen Kaifers Karl Vl. und der durch ihre seltene Schönheit weitberühmten Kaiserin Elisabeth Christina..."

Translation: Maria Theresia was born May 13, 1717 in the morning at 7:30 o'clock in Vienna as the heiress of the Roman Emperor's German Karl VI. and the far-famed-for-her-rare-beauty Empress Elisabeth Christina ... "

Previously this data had 7:28 a.m. rated C (Accuracy in question): Penfield Collection states 7 am "recorded;" not confirmed. Lescaut quotes "archives" for 7:20 AM.

Taeger IHL update 3 gives 7:32 LAT (= 7:28 LMT), from Michael Keller, who quotes 'Wienerisches Diarium' as "heute morgen wenig nach halb acht Uhr" (this morning a bit after half eight). Scholfield confirmed similar info given in "Allgemeine Staats- Kriegs- Kirchen- und Gelehrten-Chronicke" (Johann Heinrich Zedler, 1752): "und zwar nach halb 8 Uhr" (after half-past seven).
